{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}} {{Use Indian English|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox rail accident | title = Dhamara Ghat train accident | boxwidth = | image = Bihar district location map Saharsa.svg | image_alt = | caption = Location of the accident within the [[Bihar]] State | date = 19 August 2013 | time = 08:40 [[Indian Standard Time|IST]] (03:10 GMT) | location = Dhamara Ghat, [[Saharsa district]], [[Bihar]] | location-dist = | location-dist-mi = | location-dir = | location-city = | coordinates = {{Coord|25|35|25.67|N|86|35|57.95|E|display=inline,title}} | country = {{flag|India}} | line = | operator = [[Indian Railways]] | type = | cause = | trains = 1 | pax = | deaths = 37 | injuries = 24<ref>{{cite news |title=Pilgrims batter to death train driver who ploughed speeding train into 37 worshippers as they crossed tracks at packed station after morning prayer |author=Ulla Kloster |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2397249/India-train-driver-beaten-death-pilgrims-hitting-killing-37-worshipers.html |newspaper=Daily Mail |date=19 August 2013 |accessdate=20 August 2013}}</ref> | damage = 1 train<ref>{{cite news |title=India Train Accident: Speeding Train Kills 37, Angry Mob Attacks Driver |author=Indrajit Singh |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/08/19/india-train-accident_n_3777933.html |newspaper=The Huffington Post |date=19 August 2013 |accessdate=20 August 2013}}</ref> | map = | map_name = | map_state = }}
The Dhamara Ghat train accident occurred on 19 August 2013 when the [[Saharsa Patna Rajya Rani Express]] train struck a large group of people at the [[Dhamara Ghat railway station]] in the Indian state of [[Bihar]]. At least 37 people were killed and 24 were injured. The victims were mostly Hindu pilgrims returning from prayers at the nearby [[Katyayini|Katyayani]] [[mandir]].<ref>{{cite news |title=India express train in Bihar kills people crossing track |author= |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-23751270 |newspaper=BBC |date=19 August 2013 |accessdate=19 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Train Hits Hindu Pilgrims in Eastern India, Killing Dozens |author=Ellen Barry |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/08/20/world/asia/train-kills-dozens-of-religious-pilgrims-in-india.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=19 August 2013 |accessdate=19 August 2013}}</ref> The accident triggered a protest by passengers who beat the driver unconscious, attacked staff and torched two coaches of the train.<ref>{{cite news |title=Train accident leaves at 37 dead in India |author= |url=http://www.euronews.com/2013/08/19/train-accident-leaves-at-37-dead-in-india/ |newspaper=Euronews |date=19 August 2013 |accessdate=20 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=37 Killed as Train Runs Over Pilgrims in India |author=Vibhuti Agarwal |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424127887323608504579022183834734214 |newspaper=The Wall Street Journal |date=19 August 2013 |accessdate=20 August 2013}}</ref> The chief minister of Bihar State, [[Nitish Kumar]], called it "the rarest of rare tragedies". He pledged 200,000 rupees, or around $3,180, to the victims' families, and urged the railway ministry to do the same.<ref>{{cite news |title=India: at least 37 killed as express train ploughs through railway station |author=Maseeh Rahman |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/aug/19/india-killed-express-train-crash |newspaper=The Guardian |date=19 August 2013 |accessdate=20 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Angry mob beats conductor after 37 pilgrims die in Indian rail accident |author= |url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2013/08/19/35-pilgrims-die-in-indian-rail-accident/ |newspaper=Fox News |date=19 August 2013 |accessdate=20 August 2013}}</ref>
==Casualties== According to S.K. Bhardwaj, a senior Bihar police officer, 37 people lost their lives. Among them were 13 women, four children and 20 men.<ref>{{cite news |title=37 dead in Bihar railway tragedy: Nitish Kumar |author= |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/37-dead-in-Bihar-railway-tragedy-Nitish-Kumar/articleshow/21915667.cms |newspaper=The Times of India |date=19 August 2013 |accessdate=20 August 2013}}</ref> The victims were walking along the tracks at Dhamara Ghat station after disembarking from the Samastipur-Saharsa passenger train when the Saharsa-Patna Rajya Rani Express travelling at 80 km/h, struck them.<ref>{{cite news |title=Indian train runs over Hindu pilgrims, kills 37; angry mob beats driver, sets train on fire |author= |url=http://news.nationalpost.com/2013/08/19/indian-train-runs-over-hindu-pilgrims-kills-37-angry-mob-beats-driver-sets-train-on-fire/ |newspaper=National Post |date=19 August 2013 |accessdate=20 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=37 dead in India train accident |author= |url=http://www.i24news.tv/en/news/international/asia-pacific/130819-indian-train-runs-into-pilgrims-kills-37-sparks-riot |newspaper=i24news |date=19 August 2013 |accessdate=20 August 2013}}</ref>
