{{Nihongo|'''Kounotori 9'''|こうのとり9号機}}, also known as '''HTV-9''' will be the 9th flight of the [[H-II Transfer Vehicle]], an unmanned cargo spacecraft set to launch in 2020{{cn|date=August 2016}} to resupply the [[International Space Station]].<ref name=gsp-htv /><ref name=seds-20160410/><ref name=nsf-20150818 />
As currently manifested, Kounotori 9 will be the last HTV of the original model, with following missions replaced with the [[HTV-X]].<ref name=gsp-htv /><ref name=gsp-htx />
